        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-11-22 - EQ Loses it and goes on a Rampage</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p>EQ Vault recently posted a news item about an EQ Guide deciding to take out his frustration on a few fellow players. We are looking into the
details on this, we have to hope its just a prank. We will let you know.
<p><font color="#FFFF00">From EQ Vault......</font>
<p><span class="newstext">Details are still sketchy, but it appears that late last night a rogue EverQuest Guide, now most likely an ex-guide,
summoned several players to Veeshans Peak, cast a bind spell on them, and watched them die over and over again at the hands of Veeshans Peak NPCs.<br>
<br>
Afterwards, the guide responsible sent out a letter about his or her activities. This site received a copy from the ex-guide him/herself:
<blockquote>
 Hello!<br>
 <br>
 Just thought Id let you have this since you might like it. I was an EQ<br>
 Guide on the Terris Thule server. Last night (Nov 20, 2000) around 10:30pm<br>
 PST I decided to summon around 20 players to Veeshans Peak and bind them<br>
 there causing them to die many many times. For the players I didnt get a<br>
 chance to bind, I continued to summon them over and over until some big<br>
 nasty GM got mad at me, at which time my internet connection became very<br>
 unstable and disconnected me *shrug*. Included are some screenshots of the<br>
 nice event. For those of you Terris players whom I didnt get a chance to<br>
 bind: Sorry I will do better next time.<br>
 <br>
 Take care!
 <ul>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide01.jpg">Screenshot #1</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide02.jpg">Screenshot #2</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide03.jpg">Screenshot #3</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide04.jpg">Screenshot #4</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide05.jpg">Screenshot #5</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide06.jpg">Screenshot #6</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide07.jpg">Screenshot #7</a>
  <li><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/display.cgi?/eqshots/guide08.jpg">Screenshot #8</a></li>
 </ul>
</blockquote>
Its pretty clear and evident just from the letter that this guy completely lost it.<br>
<br>
Heres another report of this as sent to me by Coladar:
<blockquote>
 As some might have heard, last night at 2am eastern time, a rogue guide<br>
 started to summon and bind nearly 20 people in Veeshans Peak on Terris<br>
 Thule. The guide summoned anyone that was not anon/role above 57, in any<br>
 guild or unguilded. Those who were not bound were summoned multiple times.<br>
 <br>
 After nearly an hour multiple GMs arrived, ressed those that died one by<br>
 one, and summoned us to South Ro after we looted. We were then summoned to<br>
 Arena, given a restore of some sort, and told &quot;Have a nice day!&quot; Sadly all<br>
 of us lost multiple pixels after the restore, so the situation is far from<br>
 resolved. It is unknown why the guide did this, as they were fairly unknown<br>
 on the server. They sent out a taunt during one of my trips, not targeted<br>
 at anyone.<br>
 <br>
 There has been no official statement from Verant yet, but I am sure this<br>
 story will continue to unfold. Images I managed to take can be found at:<br>
 <br>
 <a href="http://www.swtoys.net/VP1.jpg">http://www.swtoys.net/VP1.jpg</a><br>
 <a href="http://www.swtoys.net/VP5.jpg">http://www.swtoys.net/VP5.jpg</a><br>
 <a href="http://www.swtoys.net/VP6.jpg">http://www.swtoys.net/VP6.jpg</a><br>
 <br>
 Coladar Shirlmanson<br>
 Warrior of the 57th Blade<br>
 Terris-Thule
</blockquote>
I was hoping to get a comment from Verant before running this post, but several hours have gone by since I sent the request and have received no
response.<br>
<br>
Please also dont believe this one individual represents the whole of the Guide community. While this was a horrible event for many players, the bulk
of the guides are dedicated people. Lets hope this person doesnt force Verant to tighten the rules the Guides are already bound by.</span>
<p><br>
